<title>LUXEMBOURG: Italy cannot ban French bread, EU court says.</title>
<headline>Italy cannot ban French bread, EU court says.</headline>
<dateline>LUXEMBOURG 1997-03-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Italy cannot ban French bread even if it does not comply with Italian rules, the European Court ruled on Thursday.</p>
<p>It said that even if the bread did not meet Italian moisture and ash content rules, banning its sale was still a restriction on trade which is forbidden under EU law.</p>
<p>It said the ban could not be justified on health grounds either. It was ruling on a case brought in Italy against a company which was importing bread made in France and selling it to supermarkets.</p>
<p>The court has ruled in previous cases that EU states cannot ban bread imports on the basis of their salt or dry matter content.</p>
